  "texts": [
    "Modern data privacy legislation, like GDPR, has put the burden on commercial data providers, such as or Amazon, to be more explicit as to the reasons for their processing and sharing of information.",
    "With respect to storage, holding such large databases generates unwanted disclosure risks for subjects in the case of a privacy breach.",
    "However, technological advances have led to the creation of privacy-preserving frameworks that address these concerns.",
    "Take differential privacy (Dwork 2006).",
    "This is a widely adopted industry-standard framework which involves injecting 'noise' into the data-i.e., when a database is queried, sensitive information about any set of individuals is randomly perturbed, such that any given individual is not identifiable in the dataset."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Take differential privacy (Dwork 2006)."
  ]
}